<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>

<chapter xml:id="ch-linear-inequalities" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude">
  <title>Linear Inequalities</title>

  <introduction>
    <p>
      In Grade <m>9</m>, you learned how to compare quantities using inequality symbols and solve simple inequalities involving one unknown. In this section, you will extend these skills by solving and graphing linear inequalities, working with compound inequalities, and exploring inequalities in two variables.
    </p>
    <p>
      You will learn how to represent solutions on number lines and coordinate planes, interpret and form inequalities from graphs, and apply inequalities to model and solve real-life problems involving constraints and decision-making.
    </p>
  </introduction>

